### How To Create SFTP User Without Shell Access On RHEL 8 ###

Step 1 – Create Account
-----------------------
$ sudo adduser --shell /bin/false <user>
$ sudo passwd <user>

Step 2 – Create Directory
-------------------------
$ sudo mkdir -p /var/sftp/files
$ sudo chown <user>:<group> /var/sftp/files

Note:- Set the owner and group owner of the /var/sftp to root.
$ sudo chown root:root /var/sftp
$ sudo chmod 755 /var/sftp

Step 3 – Configure SSH for SFTP - SFTP runs over the SSH protocol so configure the sshd_config file.
-------------------------------
$ sudo vim /etc/ssh/sshd_config

Match User sftpuser
	ForceCommand internal-sftp
	PasswordAuthentication yes
	ChrootDirectory /var/sftp
	PermitTunnel no
	AllowAgentForwarding no
	AllowTcpForwarding no
	X11Forwarding no

Save the configuration and restart SSH service to apply changes.
$ sudo systemctl restart sshd.service
